name: Jean Smart
summary: Actress Jean Smart made her long-awaited hosting debut on "Saturday Night Live's" 50th season premiere. Her monologue included jokes about New York City Mayor Eric Adams and a self-deprecating remark about her popularity among lesbians. The cold open featured Maya Rudolph as Vice President Kamala Harris and Dana Carvey as President Joe Biden. Smart's hosting gig was met with positive reviews, with critics praising her comedic timing and charisma. Prior to the premiere, media outlets released articles highlighting Smart's career accomplishments, vintage photos, and personal life, including information about her two children. Promotional materials for the premiere showcased Smart's desire to be the focus of the season's nostalgic opening segment. The episode was filled with surprise guests and musical performances by Jelly Roll.

name: North Carolina Hurricane
summary: Hurricane Helene has caused widespread devastation across the Southeast, leaving a trail of destruction and loss. The storm has claimed at least 65 lives and left millions without power. In North Carolina, the flooding has been particularly severe, with the state experiencing its "own Hurricane Katrina." Helene's heavy rains have led to epic flooding, with entire towns and cities submerged. The western part of the state has been hit hardest, with catastrophic damage reported in many counties. The storm's impact has extended beyond North Carolina, with flooding and damage reported in other states as well. In the aftermath of Helene, rescue crews are working tirelessly to reach stranded residents and provide assistance. The Coast Guard has deployed its "Storm Warriors" to aid in the recovery efforts. While the full extent of the damage is still being assessed, it is clear that Hurricane Helene has left a significant scar on the Southeast, and the recovery process will be long and challenging.
